2. Usage                                    
                                                                             
The X11-Basic interpreter is called >>xbasic<< (>>xbasic.exe<< under 
Windows). The compiler >>xbc<< (>>xbc.exe<< under Windows).
Under Unix these executables are usually installed in the /usr/bin/ (if 
installed via the package management system) or in /usr/local/bin 
(if installed manually from the source package) path.
Under Windows, the files are installed normally under the directory 
C:\x11basic.




